data.title: Learn to Dance, Get Fit, & Have Fun!
data.meta_description: Get to know the talented dancers, teachers, & creatives behind Dance & Co! Featuring Maks & Val Chmerkovskiy, Peta Murgatroyd, Jenna Johnson, Kiki Nyemchek, Koko Iwasaki, Emily Crouch, Taylor Banks, and many more to come!
data.meta_site_name: DANCE & CO - Learn to Dance, Get Fit, & Have Fun!
data.text:
Maksim Chmerkovskiy is a Latin Ballroom dance champion, choreographer, Broadway star and actor. Maks first appeared on Dancing with the Stars on the second season as a professional dancer. Maks was on the series for 14 seasons and won the Mirrorball Trophy in 2014 with Olympic ice dancer, Meryl D...

Peta Murgatroyd, the Two-time Mirror Ball Champion, first appeared on Dancing With The Stars in 2011 and over the past nine years has cemented herself as a fan favorite on the show, starring in over 121 episodes.

New Zealand born and raised in Australia; Peta has been dancing since the age of 4....

Jenna Johnson-Chmerkovskiy is a fan favorite from So You Think You Can Dance and Dancing With the Stars. Jenna is the season 26 Dancing With the Stars champion, which she won as a professional dancer and choreographer, partnered with Olympian Adam Rippon.

Kiki started Latin Ballroom dancing at the age of 4 and has been in the industry for 25 years. Koine “Koko” Iwasaki was born in Kanagawa, Japan and moved with her family to the United States when she was two. Koine grew up in South Florida and began dancing at the age of 3. Emily Crouch grew up in St. Louis where she trained in all styles of dance. She moved to Los Angeles in 2013 to begin her professional career signing with Clear Talent Group and dancing with Soul Escape Contemporary Dance Company. Taylor Banks, originally from the midwest, has been dancing since the age of three. She never thought a career in dance would be her path, but on a whim moved to Los Angeles after high school to see what could come of it.
